OL,3,CLord Cameron urged to heed calls to
OL,4,Canswer questions directly from MPs
OL,6,F"That is the point. It is our duty to
OL,7,Fhold ministers to account, but by
OL,8,Fdefinition in this situation, we
OL,9,Fcannot."
OL,11,FWhile Mr Galloway, who represents the
OL,12,FWorkers Party of Britain, said he did
OL,13,Fnot doubt Lord Cameron's diplomatic
OL,14,Fskills, he added: "Our problem is as a
OL,15,Fcountry ` who are forever lecturing
OL,16,Fother people on the quality of their
OL,17,Fdemocracy ` now have an unelected head
OL,18,Fof state, an unelected Prime Minister,
OL,19,Fand an unelected Foreign Secretary,
OL,20,Fthe second most important piece on the
OL,21,FTreasury bench."
