OL,4,Canswer questions directly from MPs
OL,6,FConservative MP Nigel Mills (Amber
OL,7,FValley) warned ministers current
OL,8,Farrangements were not a "tolerable
OL,9,Fsituation for the elected House to be
OL,10,Fplaced in."
OL,12,FHe added: "I think all the options we
OL,13,Fhave here are terrible, but this was
OL,14,Fnot the starting point of the
OL,15,Fcommittee or the House, this was the
OL,16,Fposition we were put in by the
OL,17,FGovernment and we were trying to find
OL,18,Fthe least bad way of fixing it."
